data: Marilyn R. Gunner Professor City College of New York 212-650-6940 Room Number: Marshak 301 mgunner@ccny.cuny.edu Website B.A., State Univ. of New York (Binghamton); Ph.D., Univ. of Pennsylvania Biophysics – theory My lab works on computational simulations of electron and proton transfers in proteins.  We are interested in proteins that carry out electron tunneling and those that transport proton across the cell membrane.  We use Monte Carlo sampling, Molecular Dynamics, DFT and network analysis.
